  "contentHtml": "\n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>Hyderabad/Bengaluru: India's Manipal Health Enterprises, backed by Singapore's <a href=\"/tag/temasek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Temasek</a>, has received approval for its stock market listing from market regulator SEBI, two sources ‌familiar ⁠with the ⁠matter told Reuters on Friday.The hospital ​chain is targeting a market debut in late ​July or early August, said the sources, who asked not to be named ​as the information has not ⁠yet been ‌made public.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>The offering ​is ​expected to be one of ⁠the largest IPOs by an Indian healthcare ​company.Manipal filed for an ​initial public offering of up to $1.2 billion in March, betting on rising demand for complex care.</p>\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        <p>The listing comes as Iran war-driven geopolitical risks have ‌fuelled a record selloff by foreign investors, which led to a ​slowdown ​in the ⁠IPO market as companies take a more cautious approach.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>Overseas investors have offloaded $29.2 billion worth ​of shares so far this year, pushing the benchmark Nifty 50 index down about 7%.(Reporting by Rishika Sadam in Hyderabad and Vivek Kumar M in Bengaluru; Editing by Joe Bavier)                    </p><!-- Category Most Read Placement -->\n                                                                    \n                                                                \n                                <ul>\n                                    \n\n                             